history.content: If you're not a declared EECS or CS major, you can't waitlist for upper division CS/EE classes in Phase 1- you can read enrolment policies here: http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Policies/enrollment.shtml
If you're not a declared EECS or CS major, you can't waitlist for upper division requirements - you can read enrolment policies here: http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Policies/enrollment.shtml

children.subject: Hi Anshul,  Unfortunately there are many majors that allow CS courses to count as upper division technical electives (math, stats, cog sci, eng math & stats, etc) and we're unable to accommodate students from these majors in phase I.
Can I talk to someone about this? These classes are also requirements for my major and I would like the policies to be changed in this case.

history.content:
Hi,
I was waitlisted for CS 170 and CS 188 but today I open up my calcentral only to see that my name has been dropped from both of these classes. I am not a CS or an EECS major as I am Engineering Math and Statistics major but these classes are my requirements too. Does someone know why this may have happened/whom should I contact about this? I have not completed CS 70 but I was planning to skip it since I have finished my lower division technical electives and have more than surpassed the need to study the CS 70 material by coming across it in my other math classes (such as Stats 134).

Thanks in advance!
